{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4405e8cc-9bb4-4da6-8367-695f58a3f5fa","content":"## The Problem\n\n**JDK 17 is too old.** .NET MAUI's current Android build tools require **JDK 21**. The bundled `android` workload targets SDK/build-tool versions that dropped JDK 17 support.\n\n## The Fix\n\n1. **Install JDK 21** (Adoptium Temurin works fine):\n   ```bash\n   brew install --cask temurin@21\n   ```\n\n2. **Update JAVA_HOME** (in `~/.zshrc` or `~/.bash_profile`):\n   ```bash\n   export JAVA_HOME=/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/temurin-21.jdk/Contents/Home\n   ```\n\n3. **Tell .NET MAUI** (if it still doesn't pick it up, add to your `.csproj`):\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <JavaSdkDirectory>/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/temurin-21.jdk/Contents/Home</JavaSdkDirectory>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\nAfter installing, verify with `java -version` showing 21.x, then rebuild.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"66201091-b3aa-4d61-b8bb-4a42ba7630c9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is having a .NET MAUI Android build failure with a Java-related error on macOS. They have Adoptium Temurin JDK 17.0.12 installed with JAVA_HOME pointing to it.\n\nLet me think about what's likely wrong here. .NET MAUI Android builds use the Android SDK build tools, which have specific Java version requirements. \n\nThe key issue is likely one of these:\n1. .NET MAUI / Android SDK requires a specific Java version (JDK 11 or JDK 17 depending on the version)\n2. The JAVA_HOME path on macOS might not be set correctly for Adoptium Temurin\n\n\n3. On macOS, Adoptium Temurin JDK 17 installs to `/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/temurin-17.jdk/Contents/Home`, and if JAVA_HOME isn't pointing there correctly, the build tools won't find Java. Since they're likely on .NET 8+ with newer Android SDK build tools that require JDK 17, the path configuration is probably the culprit here. The most likely culprits are JAVA_HOME pointing to the wrong location on macOS—it should be `/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/temurin-17.jdk/Contents/Home` for Adoptium—or the user being on .NET 9+ where JDK 21 might be needed instead of JDK 17.\n\nBut actually, .NET MAUI doesn't rely on JAVA_HOME at all; it manages Java through its own MSBuild properties and workload configuration, typically looking for the Microsoft OpenJDK installation in the Xamarin developer directory or through the `JavaSdkDirectory` property in Visual Studio for Mac.\n\nThe real issue is likely a JDK version mismatch—on .NET 9 or later, the Android SDK build tools require JDK 21, but users might have JDK 17 installed, which triggers an error during the Android build process. Given the timeline and .NET version, they almost certainly need JDK 21 instead of JDK 17. The fix is straightforward: install JDK 21, update their JAVA_HOME environment variable to point to it, or set the `JavaSdkDirectory` property in their project file. This is a knowledge question about build requirements, so I can provide the answer directly without needing to examine any files.","outputTokens":1734,"requestId":"A845:1D8045:68580E:784B0C:69FBE29F"},"id":"974c22cc-5b62-4e1a-a6de-8fd484156211","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:54:23.742Z","parentId":"d6f268d8-3d47-4bbc-a740-11f3b08ee850"}
